news.title: Maan-Mhalunge scheme to be implemented in next six months: PMRDA
news.para: On Monday, the PMRDA commissioner reviewed the project and said that work will be put on the fast track. He reviewed the 36-metre road work, which has been proposed from Hinjewadi to Mercedes-Benz International School.

news.title: Rajasthan CM pulls up civic officials for delaying lease deed distribution
news.para: The CM also announced the launch of Indira Gandhi Urban Employment Guarantee Scheme from September 9. He said 1.5 lakh people have already registered for the job.

news.title: Indore administration set to expedite realisation of RERA recovery certificates
news.para: In total 297 cases against 38 firms, RERA has estimated recovery of Rs 23.52 Crore while the responsibility of recovering the same by issuing RRC (revenue recovery certificate) to the ‘errant’ construction/development agencies.

news.title: CIDCO presents 4,158 flats for sale in Navi Mumbai
news.para: Under the mass housing scheme, 4,158 apartments located in Dronagiri, Kalamboli, Taloja and Kharghar nodes of Navi Mumbai have made available for sale at affordable rates.

news.title: You may face fate of Supertech twin towers: Bombay HC warns Integrated Realty Project
news.para: The court had last week deputed an architect to visit the site where the developer has proceeded with construction flouting a 1995 Supreme Court order and to submit a report stating up to what extent construction has been carried out.

news.title: Trehan Iris lease out three lakh sq ft at Iris Broadway mall in Gurugram
news.para: With this, the company has leased over 3 lakh sq ft so far. The leasing includes 2.5 lakh sq ft in retail and approximately 56,000 sq ft in its 4-star hotel.

news.title: Tablespace Technologies leases 1.2 million sq ft in the last six months
news.para: In one of the largest flexible office lease transactions in the country, Table Space Technologies rented 3.5 lakh sq ft office space in Outer Ring Road (ORR), Bengaluru, to Schneider Electric IT Business India, part of a French multinational company.

news.title: Mumbai: No inquiry officer yet for Bhendi Bazaar redevelopment project
news.para: ​Municipal commissioner Iqbal Chahal on Saturday had immediately issued a stop-work notice following an announcement of an inquiry by deputy chief minister Devendra Fadnavis.

news.title: Gurugram: Audit in 17 societies with structural flaws to begin in a week
news.para: The structural audit, according to sources, is likely to be completed in 45 days and the cost of the audit will be paid by the developers.

news.title: Two more full-time members appointed for UP-RERA's Greater Noida office
news.para: The UP-Rera's regional office in Greater Noida was established in 2018 with one full-time member to adjudicate cases falling in NCR districts, while two members were hearing cases in Gautam Budh Nagar and Lucknow headquarters as per roster.

news.title: Indiabulls Housing mulls raising up to Rs 1,000 crore through bonds
news.para: The fund raise plan is within the shelf limit of Rs 1,400 crore. The issue is proposed to be opened on September 5, 2022. It will be closed on September 22. The housing financier said the deemed date of allotment of bonds is fixed at September 28.

news.title: China: Country Garden Holdings' earnings slump 96% in H1 2022
news.para: Its earnings plunged to 612 million yuan ($88 million) as China's property market has "slid rapidly into severe depression", the company said in a report.

news.title: China's largest banks show wounds from property sector crisis
news.para: The first half results come after the world's second-largest economy narrowly avoided contracting in the second quarter as widespread COVID-19 lockdowns and the slumping property sector badly damaged consumer and business confidence.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: New order from LSGD gives major relief to land owners
news.para: In a major relief to the land owners whose private plots got wrongfully included under public zones in the interim development order (IDO), the local self-government department has issued an order allowing provisions to grant building permits in such plots.

news.title: Housing prices rise in 42 cities in Q1 of FY23: NHB
news.para: On a sequential basis, the 50-city index registered an expansion of 1.7 per cent in April-June 2022 against 2.6 per cent in the previous quarter, it said, adding the index is showing an increasing trend on a quarter-on-quarter basis since June 21.
